name: nur-and-marceli

text:
Hey Marceli, please meet Nur your incredible E-Mentor we've been telling you about :smile:.  Feel free to introduce yourselves, say a little bit about what you would like to get out of the mentorship and continue chatting within this channel. :wave:

I will now be leaving the channel, but please direct message myself or penny-prospela if you have any questions. All the best for now! :slightly_smiling_face:

Hi there Nur! Hope you're doing well in these weird times. Thanks so much for agreeing to be my mentor :grin: I had a look at your website and your stuff looks fantastic! I'm mostly drawn to character art that's more on the realistic side, but I'm definitely interested in stylized stuff too, and I know that it's all transferable skills. I could send you the stuff I've been working on for my showreel so far and see what you think? I'd also be really interested to hear what it's like being a freelancer, as that really doesnt get covered by my course, but I realise that there is a big demand for freelancers across animation and VFX especially. 

For sharing work, should I send stuff here? Or would you rather communicate by email? :)

Hi Marceli! Very glad to meet you!
Thank you very much for your lovely words about my works. I hope to be very helpful for your development in character modeling with my experience.
No matter if it is realistic or stylised, there are the basic rules apply to character modeling which we will examine during our journey.

Please feel free to share your samples over here. So we will see your progress from our first talk to the end.

I beileve there are many things to discuss through our chat, so no need to rush. Let’s start with your works and questions&suggestions over them.

Stay safe and healthy in this uncommon situation!:the_horns::skin-tone-2:
